is most apparent in the region off the southern\ntip of Sumatra where vortex counts were 4 times higher during periods of\nanomalous easterlies compared to periods with anomalous westerlies. In this\nregion positive (negative) ENSO and Indian-Ocean Dipole conditions drive\nanomalous easterlies (westerlies) which impact vortex formation rates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Oct 2022 22:31:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-27"}
