{"id":"2210.14547","submitter":"Filippo Fabiani","authors":"Guido Carnevale, Filippo Fabiani, Filiberto Fele, Kostas Margellos,\n  Giuseppe Notarstefano","title":"Tracking-based distributed equilibrium seeking for aggregative games","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"eess.SY cs.GT cs.SY math.OC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We propose fully-distributed algorithms for Nash equilibrium seeking in\naggregative games over networks. We first consider the case where only local\nconstraints are present and we design an algorithm combining, for each agent,\n(i) the projected pseudo-gradient descent and (ii) a tracking mechanism to\nlocally reconstruct the aggregative variable. To handle coupling constraints\narising in generalized settings, we propose another distributed algorithm based\non (i) a recently emerged augmented primal-dual scheme and (ii) two tracking\nmechanisms to reconstruct, for each agent, both the aggregative variable and\nthe coupling constraint satisfaction. Leveraging tools from singular\nperturbations analysis, we prove linear convergence to the Nash equilibrium for\nboth schemes. Finally, we run extensive numerical simulations to confirm the\neffectiveness of our methods, also showing that they outperform the current\nstate-of-the-art distributed equilibrium seeking algorithms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Oct 2022 08:08:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-27"}
